<!-- What is Semi-Solid-State -->
<section class="sec bg-white relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="section-title text-center">What Is Semi-Solid-State Battery Technology?</h2>
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">Semi-solid-state batteries replace the liquid electrolyte in traditional Li-polymer cells with a gel or semi-solid electrolyte. Often called "solid state power bank" technology in the consumer market, this next-generation chemistry fundamentally changes three things: energy density, thermal stability, and form factor.</p>

 <blockquote class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12 bg-brandOrange/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange rounded-r-xl px-6 py-5 text-sm text-slate-700 italic leading-relaxed">
  <p>"The solid-state battery market — including semi-solid-state — is projected to reach $963 million by 2030, growing at a 41.5% CAGR from $85 million in 2023. Within consumer electronics, solid-state micro batteries are forecast to grow from $1.67 billion to $3.87 billion at 14.88% CAGR. Semi-solid-state represents the first mass-production-ready step in this trajectory: delivering 50% thinner profiles, 30% higher energy density, and near-zero fire risk at only 20-40% cost premium over Li-polymer. Unlike full solid-state batteries which remain in lab/pilot phase until 2027+, semi-solid-state is shipping at scale today — and CES 2026 marked its consumer market breakout."</p>
  <cite class="block text-xs text-slate-400 mt-2 not-italic">— <a href="https://www.marketsandmarkets.com/Market-Reports/solid-state-battery-market-174849304.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">MarketsandMarkets</a>, Solid-State Battery Market Report 2025-2030; <a href="https://www.techsciresearch.com/report/solid-state-micro-battery-market/30237.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">TechSci Research</a>, Solid-State Micro Battery Market 2020-2030F</cite>
 </blockquote>

 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100 text-center">
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">50%</p>
 <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 mb-2">Thinner Profile</p>
 <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Same capacity, half the thickness. Gel electrolyte eliminates separator layers needed for liquid containment.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100 text-center">
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange mb-2">30%</p>
 <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 mb-2">Higher Energy Density</p>
 <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">More watt-hours per gram. Enables 20000mAh in a form factor that previously held 15000mAh.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100 text-center">
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">1000+</p>
 <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 mb-2">Charge Cycles</p>
 <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">1,000-2,000 cycle lifespan vs 300-500 cycles for standard Li-polymer. Gel electrolyte reduces degradation over time.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
</section>

<!-- Semi-Solid vs Li-Polymer vs Solid-State Comparison -->
<section class="sec bg-slate-50 relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-4 text-center">Semi-Solid-State vs. <span class="text-brandOrange">Li-Polymer</span> vs. Solid-State</h2>
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">Not all "solid state power bank" claims are equal. True semi-solid-state batteries use a gel electrolyte with only 2.5-10% liquid content — a production-ready middle ground between traditional lithium-polymer and full solid-state technology that won't reach mass production until 2027+.</p>

 <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <table class="w-full text-sm">
 <thead>
 <tr class="bg-white">
 <th class="p-4 text-left text-slate-500 font-bold text-xs uppercase">Parameter</th>
 <th class="p-4 text-center text-slate-500 font-bold text-xs uppercase">Li-Polymer<br><span class="text-[10px] normal-case opacity-70">Traditional</span></th>
 <th class="p-4 text-center bg-brandOrange/5 border-x border-brandOrange/20 text-brandOrange font-bold text-xs uppercase">Semi-Solid-State<br><span class="text-[10px] normal-case opacity-70">WOWOHCOOL</span></th>
 <th class="p-4 text-center text-slate-500 font-bold text-xs uppercase">Full Solid-State<br><span class="text-[10px] normal-case opacity-70">Lab/R&D</span></th>
 </tr>
 </thead>
 <tbody>
 <tr class="border-t border-slate-100">
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-700 font-semibold">Liquid Electrolyte</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center text-slate-600">60-90%</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center bg-brandOrange/5 border-x border-brandOrange/20 font-bold text-slate-900">2.5-10%</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center text-slate-600">0%</td>
 </tr>
 <tr class="border-t border-slate-100">
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-700 font-semibold">Energy Density</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center text-slate-600">180-260 Wh/kg</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center bg-brandOrange/5 border-x border-brandOrange/20 font-bold text-slate-900">280-400 Wh/kg</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center text-slate-600">400-500+ Wh/kg</td>
 </tr>
 <tr class="border-t border-slate-100">
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-700 font-semibold">Cycle Life</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center text-slate-600">300-500 cycles</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-center bg-brandOrange/5 border-x border-brandOrange/20 font-bold text-slate-900">1,000-2,000 cycles</td>
