<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="sec bg-white relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-10 text-center">Semi-Solid-State <span class="text-brandOrange">FAQ</span></h2>
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is a semi-solid-state battery power bank?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">A semi-solid-state power bank uses gel-state or semi-solid electrolyte instead of liquid electrolyte found in traditional Li-polymer batteries. This delivers 50% thinner profiles, 30% higher energy density, lower fire risk, and longer cycle life (1,000-2,000 cycles vs 300-500 for Li-polymer). Often marketed as a "solid state power bank," true semi-solid-state technology contains only 2.5-10% liquid content.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the MOQ for semi-solid-state power bank OEM?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">MOQ starts at 500 units for standard ODM models with custom logo printing. Custom OEM with tooling: 1,000-2,000 units. Sample turnaround: 3-7 days for standard, 10-15 days for custom.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Are semi-solid-state power banks safe for air shipping?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. All WOWOHCOOL semi-solid-state power banks are UN38.3 certified and meet IATA air transport regulations. Capacity up to 27,000mAh (100Wh) is allowed in carry-on luggage per IATA passenger rules.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">How is semi-solid-state different from full solid-state battery?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Semi-solid-state uses a hybrid electrolyte (partial liquid + partial solid) and is in mass production now. Full solid-state batteries are still in pilot production by manufacturers like Sunwoda and Svolt and not commercially available for power banks until 2027+.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Are semi-solid-state power banks safer than lithium-ion?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. The gel electrolyte significantly reduces thermal runaway risk compared to traditional lithium-ion or Li-polymer cells. With only 2.5-10% liquid content (vs 60-90% in Li-polymer), there is dramatically less flammable material if the cell is damaged. This aligns with the EU Battery Regulation 2023/1542 which favors low-fire-risk chemistry.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">How long does a semi-solid-state power bank last?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">WOWOHCOOL semi-solid-state power banks deliver 1,000-2,000 charge cycles before reaching 80% capacity — that's 3-4x longer than traditional Li-polymer (300-500 cycles). At one full charge per day, this translates to 3-5+ years of daily use before noticeable capacity loss.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Which brands use semi-solid-state battery technology?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Notable brands launching semi-solid-state power banks in 2025-2026 include BMX SolidSafe (US, CES 2026 winner), Kuxiu (Australia), ELECOM (Japan, 2000-cycle), Neopow (US, 285W flagship), Meenova (Kickstarter), Momax (Hong Kong), and Bull (China). Many DTC brands source semi-solid-state cells through OEM factories — WOWOHCOOL offers the same technology with full customization from MOQ 500.</p>
 </details>
